h3. Summary
When an SVN repository's branch URL is not the default, or no branches are being used, Bamboo continuously tries to perform its first-time branch detection procedure (to determine what repository branches pre-exist the build plan) and never ceases this check.

h3.Workaround
Special marker records exist in the database and these need to be removed to stop Bamboo from continuing to poll the repository.

{code:sql}
DELETE FROM VCS_BRANCH WHERE NAME='initialize.chain.branches@@!3.141519' AND CHAIN_ID=<id of BUILD plan record>;{code}

Currently the field has this note:
{quote}
This is the base URL of this installation of Bamboo. All links created (for emails etc) will be prefixed by This URL.
for example "http://derics-mbp.local:8085"
{quote}

Base URL supposedly is the URL Bamboo is accessed at. However this may be confused for the base URL Bamboo is hosted on. Extra info at the field should be added to prevent the confusion.

h3. Summary
Running mvn task with goal below, sets the system property with quotes:
{code}-Dincludes="au.*,au.com.*"{code}

Running a script task with the following inline commands, sets the system property without quotes:
{code} /usr/share/maven/bin/mvn --batch-mode -X -Djava.io.tmpdir=/opt/atlassian/bamboo/temp/TEST-CLON-JOB1 clean package -Dincludes="au.*,au.com.*"{code}

h3. Expected Results
Consistency between the script task and the Maven task

h3. Actual Results
When running maven with -X from Maven task:
{code}
build	29-Jun-2016 15:50:56	[DEBUG] Setting system property [includes]=["au.*,au.com.*"]
{code}
When running maven with -X from Script task:
{code}
build	29-Jun-2016 15:51:03	[DEBUG] Setting system property [includes]=[au.*,au.com.*]
{code}
 
h3.Workaround
Remove quotes from the system property in the Maven task goals.

